    "### 1.9 Personal Ethical Concern\n",
    "\n",
    "My primary ethical concern is **automated exclusion**. If the model consistently predicts certain demographic groups as unlikely to convert, marketing teams may systematically exclude those groups from campaigns. Over time, this creates a feedback loop, so excluded users never get the chance to convert, reinforcing the model's bias. This is why gender-based fairness monitoring (and potentially by income bracket) is essential, and why human oversight should remain part of any deployment."
   ]
