    "## 2. Hypothesis\n",
    "\n",
    "Based on domain understanding of digital marketing, the following hypotheses will guide the analysis:\n",
    "\n",
    "**H1 — Engagement drives conversion:** Customers with higher website engagement (more pages per visit, longer time on site, more website visits) are significantly more likely to convert.\n",
    "\n",
    "**H2 — Channel effectiveness varies:** Certain campaign channels (e.g., PPC, Email) produce higher conversion rates than others (e.g., Awareness campaigns via Social Media).\n",
    "\n",
    "**H3 — Behavioral signals outweigh demographics:** Features like AdSpend, WebsiteVisits, and EmailClicks are stronger predictors of conversion than Age, Gender, or Income.\n",
    "\n",
    "These hypotheses will be tested during exploratory data analysis and validated through feature importance analysis after model training."
   ]
