    "## 4.11 Data Leakage Prevention\n",
    "\n",
    "Data leakage occurs when information from the future or the target variable inadvertently appears in your features. It inflates validation scores, gives false confidence, and leads to models that fail in production.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Type | What It Means | Prevention |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Target Leakage | Features include direct or indirect info from the target | Never include post-outcome data as features |\n",
    "| Temporal Leakage | Model sees future data it shouldn't have access to | Use cutoff timestamps to filter features |\n",
    "| Preprocessing Leakage | Scaling or imputation fit on full dataset before splitting | Fit preprocessing only on training data |\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.11.1 Automated Leakage Scan"
   ]
  },
